<s>Notice the feeling in your body.</s>
<break time="2500ms"/>
<s>Something has shifted. Something subtle, but real.</s>
</p>

<break time="3000ms"/>

<!-- Deepening Explanation -->
<p>
<s>What's happening inside you right now is neurochemistry.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>The extended exhale has stimulated your vagus nerve.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>This long nerve runs from your brain, through your chest, into your abdomen.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>It's the main communication line between your mind and body.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>When you breathe this way, you're telling your nervous system: all is well. We are safe.</s>
</p>

<break time="2500ms"/>

<p>
<s>The holds between breaths are training something else.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>They're building your carbon dioxide tolerance.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>People who panic easily often have low CO2 tolerance.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>The slightest discomfort triggers alarm.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>With practice, you expand your window of tolerance.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>You become less reactive. More stable. More calm.</s>
</p>

<break time="3000ms"/>

