<!-- Integration Section -->
<p>
<s>Beautiful.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>You've completed sixteen cycles of box breathing.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>Your nervous system has shifted.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>Your baseline has lowered.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>This is not imagination. This is physiology.</s>
</p>

<break time="2500ms"/>

<p>
<s>Take a moment now to appreciate what you've done.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>You didn't wait for calm to find you.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>You created it. Deliberately. Skillfully.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>This is power. True power. The kind that can't be taken from you.</s>
</p>

<break time="3000ms"/>

<!-- Practical Application -->
<p>
<s>Let me share when to use this technique in your daily life.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>Before any high-stakes situation. A presentation. An interview. A difficult conversation.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>Find a quiet moment. Even a bathroom stall will do.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>Four to five rounds is enough to shift your state.</s>
</p>

<break time="2000ms"/>

<p>
<s>When anxiety rises unexpectedly.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>When you feel the familiar tightening in your chest, the racing of your thoughts.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>Start breathing. Don't wait for permission. Don't wait for the perfect moment.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>The technique works anywhere. Anytime. No one even needs to know.</s>
</p>

<break time="2500ms"/>

<p>
<s>And as a daily practice.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>Five minutes each morning, before the day begins.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>This creates a higher baseline. A calmer foundation.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>Stressors that used to knock you off balance will barely register.</s>
</p>

<break time="3000ms"/>

